1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,136
=Episode 28=

3
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:15,240
(The individuals involved
in these three incidents are unrelated.)

4
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,920
(The only common factor
was this fingerprint.)

5
00:02:18,321 --> 00:02:20,601
(It's currently unclear
what this means.)

6
00:02:21,041 --> 00:02:22,881
(But given Liu Xiaofeng's fall,)

7
00:02:23,161 --> 00:02:24,561
(we have reason to believe)

8
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:27,001
(that the fingerprints
were not accidental.)

9
00:03:04,632 --> 00:03:10,256
(Yu Xiao'ou just died. Why Xia Tian,
her "best friend", starts a new life?)

10
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:43,561
On November 24th last year,

11
00:03:43,841 --> 00:03:46,041
someone from Dragonview Manor
called the police,

12
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,800
claiming there was a gas leak

13
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,281
with an imminent risk of explosion.

14
00:03:49,721 --> 00:03:50,960
After receiving the call,

15
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:54,041
the police responded
with property, gas, and fire personnel.

16
00:03:55,721 --> 00:03:57,321
During the evacuation of residents,

17
00:03:57,321 --> 00:04:01,561
Cheng Jianmin of Building 9, Unit 1102,
was found dead.

18
00:04:04,441 --> 00:04:06,640
Cheng Jianmin, male, 70 years old,

19
00:04:06,881 --> 00:04:09,760
lived at Unit 1102, Building 9,
Dragonview Manor.

20
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,520
(Cheng Jianmin's living room)
He lived alone.

21
00:04:11,321 --> 00:04:13,841
Property management and police

22
00:04:13,841 --> 00:04:15,080
went door to door at the scene.

23
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,841
They received no response
from this unit.

24
00:04:16,841 --> 00:04:20,560
They forced entry and found
Cheng Jianmin collapsed on the sofa.

25
00:04:21,041 --> 00:04:24,440
Property staff and police officers
administered first aid on the spot,

26
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,601
but couldn't save him.

27
00:04:26,521 --> 00:04:27,880
Later, the emergency was declared.

28
00:04:28,281 --> 00:04:29,961
The gas leak was a false alarm.

29
00:04:30,761 --> 00:04:32,201
Medical personnel arrived then,

30
00:04:32,201 --> 00:04:35,961
and determined Cheng Jianmin had died
before the property staff forced entry.

31
00:04:35,961 --> 00:04:37,961
The cause of death was likely
a heart attack.

32
00:04:39,201 --> 00:04:42,721
Here are pictures of some medications
Cheng Jianmin used daily.

33
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,041
Given that Cheng Jianmin
was on long-term medication

34
00:04:46,401 --> 00:04:48,641
and was an ill heart patient
with limited mobility,

35
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:51,000
the incident was ruled
as a sudden illness.

36
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,240
His children also raised no objections.

37
00:04:56,761 --> 00:04:59,161
What's the situation
with Cheng Jianmin's children?

38
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:00,841
I looked into it.

39
00:05:00,841 --> 00:05:03,641
Cheng Jianmin's wife
passed away many years ago.

40
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:05,480
Cheng Jianmin never remarried.

41
00:05:05,841 --> 00:05:07,641
They had two sons and one daughter.

42
00:05:07,641 --> 00:05:08,761
They had their own families.

43
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:10,560
The daughter lives abroad.

44
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,800
The two sons live here.

45
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,992
Cheng Jianmin collapsed
so close to these medications.

46
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:17,281
(Cheng Jianmin's death scene)
Didn't he get to use them?

47
00:05:17,721 --> 00:05:19,961
I suspect the attack was too sudden.

48
00:05:19,961 --> 00:05:21,201
He didn't have time.

49
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,641
Viewed this way, it seems like
a common occurrence.

50
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:28,281
Were there any other anomalies
at the scene?

51
00:05:28,521 --> 00:05:31,281
No signs of a struggle or fight
were found at the scene.

52
00:05:31,281 --> 00:05:32,560
No loss of property, either.

53
00:05:34,641 --> 00:05:37,761
This is an emergency alert device, right?
Connected to the community office.

54
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:39,920
Also very close to him.

55
00:05:40,761 --> 00:05:41,360
Never used?

56
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,000
Probably not.

57
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,480
Regarding the follow-up,

58
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,601
a social worker did raise an objection.

59
00:05:47,041 --> 00:05:49,680
First, she didn't receive
a distress call from Cheng Jianmin.

60
00:05:49,761 --> 00:05:52,841
Second, the heater would cause him
chest tightness and shortness of breath.

61
00:05:52,841 --> 00:05:53,641
So he never used it.

62
00:05:53,641 --> 00:05:56,281
Yet, the heater was on that day.

63
00:05:56,841 --> 00:06:00,281
This social worker mainly took care
of seniors living alone.

64
00:06:00,281 --> 00:06:02,201
She was quite familiar
with Cheng Jianmin.

65
00:06:02,201 --> 00:06:04,161
It was due to her persistence

66
00:06:04,161 --> 00:06:07,680
that our colleagues conducted
a brief search of Cheng Jianmin's home.

67
00:06:08,281 --> 00:06:10,081
But nothing suspicious was found.

68
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,761
Where was that fingerprint found?

69
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:14,761
On the AC remote control.

70
00:06:15,521 --> 00:06:18,480
However, Cheng Jianmin employed
an hourly cleaner,

71
00:06:18,641 --> 00:06:20,081
who came every week to clean.

72
00:06:20,081 --> 00:06:22,041
Finding outsider's fingerprints
is quite normal.

73
00:06:22,081 --> 00:06:23,281
No anomalies after all.

74
00:06:23,281 --> 00:06:24,761
So the matter wasn't pursued further.

75
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:28,521
But later, same fingerprints were found
in connection with three separate cases,

76
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,841
prompting attention
from the investigating units.

77
00:06:30,841 --> 00:06:32,120
The investigation was reopened.

78
00:06:48,521 --> 00:06:49,201
Hello.

79
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:50,360
Have a seat.

80
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:52,680
This incident happened
quite a while ago.

81
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,961
Why are you still investigating?

82
00:06:54,721 --> 00:06:56,560
Wasn't it concluded
that there were no issues?

83
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,841
We heard you were quite familiar
with Cheng Jianmin's situation.

84
00:07:00,161 --> 00:07:01,360
We're here today

85
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,440
to ask you to walk us through about it.

86
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,201
No trouble at all.

87
00:07:05,401 --> 00:07:07,120
I should cooperate with the police.

88
00:07:07,680 --> 00:07:10,201
It's just that it's been a long time.

89
00:07:10,201 --> 00:07:12,320
I'm afraid I might not remember
many details clearly.

90
00:07:12,961 --> 00:07:15,480
I remember when I arrived that day,

91
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,800
the ambulance was already there.

92
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,120
It was very chaotic at the time.

93
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:23,761
What was Cheng Jianmin's relationship
with his children like?

94
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,920
Well, you've hit the nail on the head.

95
00:07:26,641 --> 00:07:27,961
Those children of Cheng...

96
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:33,161
His daughter got her green card early
and settled abroad.

97
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:36,521
The two sons are here locally,

98
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,721
and they are quite rich.

99
00:07:39,601 --> 00:07:41,021
But none of them

100
00:07:41,021 --> 00:07:44,201
want to live with and take care
of their old man.

101
00:07:45,281 --> 00:07:46,000
Cheng was also

102
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,440
a bit impatient,

103
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,201
with a temper.

104
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:51,240
What conflicts did they have?

105
00:07:53,521 --> 00:07:54,521
Cheng

106
00:07:54,641 --> 00:07:57,161
used to be in real estate development.

107
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,880
His company wasn't as big
as those major enterprises,

108
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,201
but it was still substantial.

109
00:08:01,401 --> 00:08:03,320
Now, he's handing it over
to the next generation.

110
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,641
How much should each get?

111
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,240
Why give to one but not the other?

112
00:08:07,841 --> 00:08:09,161
I heard his two sons

113
00:08:09,161 --> 00:08:12,201
even fought a lawsuit
over inheriting the business.

114
00:08:13,761 --> 00:08:15,240
Well, I just remembered something.

115
00:08:16,120 --> 00:08:19,081
On the day Cheng died,

116
00:08:19,521 --> 00:08:20,641
the elder son, younger son,

117
00:08:20,641 --> 00:08:24,000
and their wives got
into a big argument right downstairs.

118
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:24,920
It even went physical.

119
00:08:27,680 --> 00:08:28,641
How did it get physical?

120
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:29,081
What?

121
00:08:29,081 --> 00:08:29,880
Stop arguing!

122
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,720
What's your problem?

123
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:35,121
What are you arguing about?

124
00:08:35,641 --> 00:08:36,361
Stop it!

125
00:08:36,361 --> 00:08:37,320
Dad, stay out of this.

126
00:08:37,976 --> 00:08:39,600
Still arguing with the old man here?

127
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,720
- Stop it!
- Let go!

128
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:41,401
Listen up.

129
00:08:41,401 --> 00:08:41,920
Let go!

130
00:08:42,401 --> 00:08:43,320
Stop this!

131
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,320
Let go!

132
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,200
Calm down first.

133
00:08:45,481 --> 00:08:46,241
Stay calm.

134
00:08:46,241 --> 00:08:47,401
- Talk it out!
- Calm down!

135
00:08:47,401 --> 00:08:48,481
You're family! Why fight?

136
00:08:48,481 --> 00:08:49,320
All because of you!

137
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:51,080
After the old man got inside,

138
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:52,960
they were too embarrassed
to keep arguing.

139
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,521
The old man's health was usually poor,

140
00:08:55,881 --> 00:08:58,361
but he seemed fine that day.

141
00:08:58,761 --> 00:09:01,121
Were his children satisfied
with how it was handled?

142
00:09:01,121 --> 00:09:03,001
They all thought I was overstepping,

143
00:09:03,481 --> 00:09:05,600
pressuring me to issue
the death certificate quickly.

144
00:09:05,761 --> 00:09:07,401
They wanted to sell the house fast.

145
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,761
Did they sell it?

146
00:09:09,241 --> 00:09:10,001
Of course, not.

147
00:09:10,121 --> 00:09:11,960
Cheng has a daughter overseas, right?

148
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:13,320
She refused to come back

149
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,720
and wouldn't cooperate with them
on the notarization.

150
00:09:15,840 --> 00:09:17,600
She was just dragging it out.

151
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:21,001
Do you know about Cheng Jianmin's
social connections?

152
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,521
I don't know much about that.

153
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,320
Had he used the emergency alert device

154
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,521
in his room before?

155
00:09:29,241 --> 00:09:30,121
Yes.

156
00:09:30,241 --> 00:09:31,720
Multiple times, actually.

157
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:33,840
But it was usually false alarms.

158
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:35,800
He took it very seriously.

159
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:39,680
If anything seemed slightly off,

160
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:40,761
he'd call us immediately.

161
00:09:40,761 --> 00:09:43,560
That's why I found it strange this time.

162
00:09:43,641 --> 00:09:45,641
Why didn't he call us?

163
00:09:47,161 --> 00:09:50,200
Let's discuss the heating issue.

164
00:09:51,401 --> 00:09:52,361
Oh, that...

165
00:09:53,281 --> 00:09:56,041
When I rushed over that day,

166
00:09:56,641 --> 00:09:58,440
I noticed his room was extremely hot.

167
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,560
The temperature was high.

168
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:00,920
All heaters were on.

169
00:10:01,121 --> 00:10:04,241
Our community uses
centralized electric heating.

170
00:10:04,241 --> 00:10:05,041
Electric-powered.

171
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:08,361
Cheng usually avoided heating
because it made him feel suffocated.

172
00:10:08,361 --> 00:10:10,241
Neighbors above and below complained.

173
00:10:10,440 --> 00:10:12,641
His refusal affected
their temperatures too.

174
00:10:12,761 --> 00:10:14,761
They even confronted him
at home over it.

175
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:15,761
Caused some friction.

176
00:10:17,001 --> 00:10:18,560
Later, my supervisor told me,

177
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:21,720
"Maybe Cheng just felt cold suddenly."

178
00:10:22,241 --> 00:10:24,121
I realized my supervisor had a point.

179
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:26,161
I overreacted.

180
00:10:30,401 --> 00:10:31,761
Alright, Ms. Zhao.

181
00:10:32,001 --> 00:10:33,800
That's all for today.

182
00:10:34,320 --> 00:10:35,041
Thank you.

183
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:35,840
You're welcome.

184
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,001
Happy to assist.

185
00:10:37,001 --> 00:10:37,521
Okay.

186
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:38,881
Thanks.

187
00:10:38,881 --> 00:10:39,761
- Okay.
- Thanks.

188
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,041
Hello?

189
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:46,200
If Cheng Jianmin's family comes,
question them first.

190
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:49,481
Send me the phone number and address.

191
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,560
Got it.

192
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:57,600
We found the person
who reported the gas leak last time.

193
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,680
We need to go there now.

194
00:11:00,361 --> 00:11:02,241
Master, do you think
that caller is suspicious?

195
00:11:02,761 --> 00:11:03,401
Hard to tell.

196
00:11:05,481 --> 00:11:08,001
You haven't taken leave
in a while, right?

197
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,521
Visit your parents when you can.

198
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,121
Appreciate your concern.

199
00:11:14,121 --> 00:11:16,560
Still swamped with cases.

200
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,281
I'll go later.

201
00:11:17,281 --> 00:11:17,761
Alright.

202
00:11:38,121 --> 00:11:39,440
These two are unbelievable.

203
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,521
Fighting anywhere, anytime.

204
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,041
Is it really worth it?

205
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:44,521
Is it worth it?

206
00:11:45,481 --> 00:11:46,481
I'm telling you.

207
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:47,920
This is not a small amount.

208
00:11:48,121 --> 00:11:50,001
That Dragonview Manor apartment,

209
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:52,121
I bet you couldn't afford it
in your lifetime.

210
00:11:52,920 --> 00:11:54,761
But judging from motives,

211
00:11:54,761 --> 00:11:56,401
they are not suspicious.

212
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:57,680
There's no will.

213
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:00,920
He passes away like this,
and it gets even messier.

214
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,960
Do you think this is actually a case?

215
00:12:04,361 --> 00:12:06,080
So far, nothing seems off.

216
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,881
Just an unidentified fingerprint.

217
00:12:08,761 --> 00:12:09,641
Keep investigating.

218
00:12:09,641 --> 00:12:11,521
Cheng Jianmin is in real estate,

219
00:12:11,521 --> 00:12:13,001
with complicated social connections.

220
00:12:13,001 --> 00:12:15,600
We might actually dig something up.

221
00:12:16,161 --> 00:12:16,840
Okay.

222
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:18,552
(Mobile Parcel Service Truck)

223
00:12:28,320 --> 00:12:29,401
Cheng Xiaowei, right?

224
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,720
City CID.

225
00:12:34,881 --> 00:12:35,761
CID officers?

226
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:36,920
Looking for me?

227
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:41,361
Is this your phone number?

228
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:44,481
Yes, it's mine.

229
00:12:44,641 --> 00:12:46,440
It's a company-issued work phone.

230
00:12:46,881 --> 00:12:48,600
On November 24th last year,

231
00:12:49,001 --> 00:12:50,241
you used this number

232
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:54,560
to report a gas leak
at Dragonview Manor. Remember?

233
00:12:54,761 --> 00:12:55,840
Last year...

234
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:57,641
Yes.

235
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,641
There was a gas leak incident there.

236
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:02,361
But I wasn't the one who called it in.

237
00:13:02,361 --> 00:13:04,960
The log shows it came from your number.

238
00:13:06,121 --> 00:13:07,200
The number is mine,

239
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,320
but I didn't make that call.

240
00:13:09,241 --> 00:13:11,161
Someone borrowed my phone that day.

241
00:13:11,161 --> 00:13:12,920
Said there was a gas leak at home.

242
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,761
Forgot to bring a phone when left home.

243
00:13:16,361 --> 00:13:18,121
Remember anything about that person?

244
00:13:21,241 --> 00:13:22,200
That person...

245
00:13:24,281 --> 00:13:25,241
Can't recall clearly.

246
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:26,600
It was a woman.

247
00:13:28,521 --> 00:13:29,800
Pretty average-looking.

248
00:13:33,361 --> 00:13:34,241
This one?

249
00:13:35,361 --> 00:13:36,440
Body shape matches.

250
00:13:36,881 --> 00:13:37,960
But I can't be sure.

251
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:41,001
We deal with tons
of people daily in this job.

252
00:13:41,361 --> 00:13:43,320
What did she do after calling?

253
00:13:43,881 --> 00:13:46,560
She handed my phone back
after reporting.

254
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:47,600
Then left.

255
00:13:49,001 --> 00:13:50,361
No idea where she went.

256
00:13:52,161 --> 00:13:52,960
Take your time.

257
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:54,920
Think about it.

258
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:59,121
See what else comes to mind.

259
00:14:01,041 --> 00:14:01,881
There's something.

260
00:14:02,161 --> 00:14:04,161
But I'm not sure if it's related.

261
00:14:04,641 --> 00:14:07,080
Cops and firefighters showed up fast.

262
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,361
And the place got chaotic.

263
00:14:10,161 --> 00:14:11,440
Someone swiped my vest.

264
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,200
Vest?

265
00:14:13,161 --> 00:14:14,001
What kind of vest?

266
00:14:16,401 --> 00:14:17,200
Like this one.

267
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:18,840
Company-issued.

268
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:21,121
Mandatory uniform for work.

269
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:23,080
Cheap material.

270
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,521
Can't imagine why anyone'd steal it.

271
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:27,481
Thanks.

272
00:14:37,641 --> 00:14:38,440
Off work?

273
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:40,121
That's early.

274
00:14:40,281 --> 00:14:42,001
Early? It's already dark.

275
00:14:43,241 --> 00:14:44,121
Got a date?

276
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:45,881
Class reunion.

277
00:14:46,041 --> 00:14:47,200
Do I look okay?

278
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:47,840
Looks good.

279
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:49,041
Well...

280
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:51,320
Oh, right. I was just
about to bring this to you.

281
00:14:51,521 --> 00:14:52,521
Results are in.

282
00:14:52,761 --> 00:14:54,361
The fiber samples you collected

283
00:14:54,361 --> 00:14:57,161
and fibers
from Liu Xiaofeng's fall scene

284
00:14:58,121 --> 00:15:01,521
are identical in color,
material, and hardness.

285
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:06,920
It means the fiber at the fall scene

286
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,440
came from a courier's vest?

287
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:10,720
Can't say for sure.

288
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:13,641
Because other companies
use this fabric too.

289
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,600
But it's a useful reference.

290
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,521
If you locate that vest,

291
00:15:17,521 --> 00:15:19,001
I can run a comparison.

292
00:15:20,401 --> 00:15:21,521
It's late. I'll head out.

293
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:22,560
Stay safe.

294
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:23,600
Bye.

295
00:15:28,361 --> 00:15:29,361
I made some inquiries.

296
00:15:29,361 --> 00:15:31,440
Regarding Cheng Jianmin's
small real estate firm,

297
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:33,361
despite the power struggle
between his sons,

298
00:15:33,481 --> 00:15:35,320
the operations are solid overall.

299
00:15:35,560 --> 00:15:36,960
Employee benefits are decent.

300
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:39,481
Staff speak well of him too.

301
00:15:40,361 --> 00:15:42,440
Real estate breeds disputes

302
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:44,121
and makes enemies easily.

303
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:48,401
But when Cheng Jianmin ran things,

304
00:15:48,401 --> 00:15:49,641
he was well-liked.

305
00:15:49,641 --> 00:15:53,161
Never heard of him having any grudges
or disputes with anyone.

306
00:15:53,761 --> 00:15:54,641
By the way, Qian,

307
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:56,521
how's the caller's investigation?

308
00:15:58,121 --> 00:16:00,121
We can basically confirm
it was a false report.

309
00:16:01,121 --> 00:16:05,200
I suspect the goal was to get
Cheng Jianmin's body found quickly.

310
00:16:06,361 --> 00:16:07,320
That doesn't make sense.

311
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:10,560
Logically, wouldn't they
want it found as late as possible?

312
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:12,001
Exactly.

313
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:18,001
Let's assume that call is connected
to Cheng Jianmin's death.

314
00:16:18,161 --> 00:16:20,920
And Cheng Jianmin's death
wasn't a real accident.

315
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,521
So, the later it's found,

316
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:26,320
the more likely it would be mistaken
as a natural death, right?

317
00:16:27,241 --> 00:16:29,281
What killer would want to be discovered?

318
00:16:29,281 --> 00:16:30,001
Alright.

319
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:31,401
It's late.

320
00:16:31,401 --> 00:16:31,920
Captain Leng.

321
00:16:32,521 --> 00:16:33,041
Master.

322
00:16:33,041 --> 00:16:34,641
You should head home and get some rest.

323
00:16:35,041 --> 00:16:37,761
Tomorrow, you and Long go back
to the homestay scene.

324
00:16:39,001 --> 00:16:40,440
We're dropping Cheng Jianmin's case?

325
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:43,001
No. But we can't put all our eggs
in one basket.

326
00:16:43,241 --> 00:16:46,241
Assign a few people to keep digging
into Cheng Jianmin's social connections.

327
00:16:46,241 --> 00:16:47,080
Yes.

328
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:49,920
The rest of you,
get ready for the next case.

329
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,560
Dismissed. Get some rest, now.

330
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:52,521
Yes, sir.

331
00:16:52,521 --> 00:16:54,161
Come. Need to talk to you
about something.

332
00:17:12,600 --> 00:17:15,512
(Martyr Chen Yumo's Tomb)

333
00:17:18,761 --> 00:17:20,320
See the painting I made for you?

334
00:17:22,001 --> 00:17:24,681
It's in your favorite Rembrandt style.

335
00:17:25,761 --> 00:17:26,921
I'd never tried it before.

336
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:29,921
This time, I realized it's really hard.

337
00:17:31,761 --> 00:17:33,441
You'll probably laugh at how bad it is.

338
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,160
But that's okay.

339
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,160
I've picked up the brush again now.

340
00:17:40,041 --> 00:17:41,041
If it's not good,

341
00:17:41,521 --> 00:17:42,600
I can just keep practicing.

342
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:27,521
You're late.

343
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:32,721
Found anything?

344
00:18:34,201 --> 00:18:36,400
Nothing significant.

345
00:18:36,521 --> 00:18:39,201
This homestay
is in the middle of nowhere.

346
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:41,360
I just did a rough estimate

347
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:43,400
of the area this camera can cover.

348
00:18:48,961 --> 00:18:50,001
Police?

349
00:18:50,441 --> 00:18:51,721
I've been waiting for you.

350
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:01,041
Your homestay is out of the way.

351
00:19:01,921 --> 00:19:02,521
Yes.

352
00:19:05,281 --> 00:19:06,241
I'll take you to see it.

353
00:19:06,721 --> 00:19:07,840
The scenery here is great.

354
00:19:08,241 --> 00:19:10,160
Lots of city folks come here for it.

355
00:19:12,761 --> 00:19:13,600
It's right up ahead.

356
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,840
This path isn't easy to walk.

357
00:19:18,961 --> 00:19:20,201
You'll get used to it.

358
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,120
Has anything been moved?

359
00:19:25,521 --> 00:19:26,201
No.

360
00:19:26,201 --> 00:19:27,921
It costs money
to have someone move things.

361
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:29,921
Besides, who'd want to do that?

362
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:34,721
You know what?

363
00:19:34,721 --> 00:19:36,360
I'm cursed with the worst luck

364
00:19:36,360 --> 00:19:37,761
to get such a guest.

365
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:40,481
My homestay just opened a few days ago,

366
00:19:40,481 --> 00:19:41,600
and now this happens!

367
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,400
Someone died in this room!

368
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,961
Who will be willing to stay here now?

369
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:49,041
How much do you know
about the deceased, Zhou Lianqin?

370
00:19:49,041 --> 00:19:50,281
I didn't know him.

371
00:19:50,441 --> 00:19:51,681
He just gave a phone number.

372
00:19:51,681 --> 00:19:53,921
The name on the reservation
wasn't even his.

373
00:19:54,201 --> 00:19:55,001
Who booked it?

374
00:19:55,681 --> 00:19:57,640
I figure his family booked it for him.

375
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:58,840
They placed the order online.

376
00:19:58,961 --> 00:20:00,201
Paid for it online.

377
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,560
Then he just came
to get the key and stay.

378
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,521
If I'd known he was
a pyramid scheme runner on the lam,

379
00:20:05,521 --> 00:20:06,961
a deadbeat shown on TV,

380
00:20:07,241 --> 00:20:09,320
I'd never in a million years
have rented to him!

381
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:12,360
Alive, he cheated and scammed people,

382
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,800
and dead, he couldn't even find
some deserted spot

383
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,201
and had to come here to haunt me?

384
00:20:19,481 --> 00:20:20,921
Has anyone touched this up here?

385
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:22,521
No.

386
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:25,800
Describe the situation back then.

387
00:20:26,281 --> 00:20:28,001
I wasn't there when it happened.

388
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:30,600
His family couldn't reach him,

389
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,921
so they called me and rushed over.

390
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:35,281
Was Zhou Lianqin alone in the room
those few days?

391
00:20:35,281 --> 00:20:36,320
I don't know.

392
00:20:36,961 --> 00:20:38,521
He booked the place for a week.

393
00:20:38,961 --> 00:20:41,281
Said he preferred not to be disturbed.

394
00:20:41,281 --> 00:20:43,241
No need for housekeeping to clean often.

395
00:20:43,761 --> 00:20:45,640
He paid upfront willingly.

396
00:20:45,640 --> 00:20:46,600
No haggling.

397
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,800
It was the off-season,
so I rented it to him.

398
00:20:49,001 --> 00:20:49,800
When I got here,

399
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,921
the door was locked from the inside.

400
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:54,120
A window was open a crack,
so I climbed in.

401
00:20:54,120 --> 00:20:55,288
I came in, went over here,

402
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:57,560
and he was hanging right here.

403
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:58,880
So scary.

404
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,320
You got him down?

405
00:21:00,481 --> 00:21:01,721
How would I dare do that?

406
00:21:02,201 --> 00:21:03,360
I called an ambulance.

407
00:21:04,201 --> 00:21:05,521
His family took him down.

408
00:21:05,521 --> 00:21:06,640
After the ambulance arrived,

409
00:21:06,961 --> 00:21:09,761
they said he'd been dead
for several hours.

410
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:11,921
I just didn't expect

411
00:21:11,921 --> 00:21:14,281
a hanged person would be like this.

412
00:21:14,281 --> 00:21:15,560
Made everything all messy.

413
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:20,201
Alright, do whatever you want.

414
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:22,320
I'm leaving.
Call me if you need anything.

415
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:24,120
Oh, my.

416
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:30,120
Found anything?

417
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:34,441
There are obvious friction marks
on the beam.

418
00:21:36,001 --> 00:21:37,681
My theory is

419
00:21:39,001 --> 00:21:42,481
that during self-hanging,
the body instinctively sways.

420
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:47,681
Thus, the rope rubs against the beam,
leaving marks.

421
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:51,001
This is key to determining
if he was alive when hanged.

422
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,400
Because the deceased was heavy,

423
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:55,481
the friction marks are deeper.

424
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:57,840
At first glance, it seems fine,

425
00:21:57,840 --> 00:22:00,160
but closer inspection reveals

426
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,721
traces of rope fibers
at the base of the marks.

427
00:22:03,721 --> 00:22:05,640
And the fibers are aligned uniformly.

428
00:22:06,721 --> 00:22:10,320
But instinctive body movements
cause irregular friction.

429
00:22:10,681 --> 00:22:13,600
Only consistent,
forward pulling of the rope

430
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,201
would produce this pattern.

431
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:18,880
No wonder the investigating unit
labeled it suspected suicide.

432
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,041
Homicide can't be ruled out.

433
00:22:20,961 --> 00:22:23,160
The victim was hung up by someone else.

434
00:22:23,481 --> 00:22:25,400
The family insisted on an autopsy then.

435
00:22:26,120 --> 00:22:31,961
The death report listed cerebral edema
from carotid occlusion.

436
00:22:33,201 --> 00:22:37,400
The neck ligature marks
are also consistent with hanging.

437
00:22:38,961 --> 00:22:40,761
If my hypothesis is correct,

438
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:46,001
I suspect the victim was semi-conscious

439
00:22:46,001 --> 00:22:47,961
when the noose was placed
and he was hoisted.

440
00:22:48,201 --> 00:22:49,681
But to pull this off,

441
00:22:49,681 --> 00:22:52,001
the killer must weigh
at least as much as the victim.

442
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:57,600
Zhou Lianqin weighed nearly 100kg.

443
00:22:58,281 --> 00:22:59,961
A killer heavier than him...

444
00:23:01,921 --> 00:23:03,001
There's another possibility

445
00:23:04,080 --> 00:23:07,320
that he used a pulley or similar tool.

446
00:23:28,961 --> 00:23:30,441
Where was that fingerprint found?

447
00:23:32,481 --> 00:23:33,800
Next to the ligature mark.

448
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:57,481
This is the only person who entered

449
00:23:57,521 --> 00:23:59,201
after Zhou checked in,
before the incident.

450
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,201
And he wasn't seen leaving.

451
00:24:01,681 --> 00:24:05,001
He likely left
through the back window, as you said.

452
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:06,840
Can you zoom in more?

453
00:24:07,961 --> 00:24:09,201
I can,

454
00:24:09,481 --> 00:24:11,360
but see how covered up he is?

455
00:24:12,241 --> 00:24:15,800
I compared this with Gao Liang's photo.

456
00:24:16,201 --> 00:24:17,001
Look.

457
00:24:17,800 --> 00:24:20,041
Here, sunglasses hide the eyes.

458
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,441
Here, only the eyes are visible.

459
00:24:23,241 --> 00:24:26,400
Data-wise, I can't confirm
it's the same person.

460
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:31,241
But physically, they share similarities.

461
00:24:31,241 --> 00:24:32,560
Strong similarities, actually.

462
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:34,241
Both over 180 cm tall,

463
00:24:34,241 --> 00:24:35,241
lean build.

464
00:24:44,521 --> 00:24:45,160
Captain Leng.

465
00:24:46,041 --> 00:24:47,160
This is Wen Yong's wife.

466
00:24:47,521 --> 00:24:49,560
This is Captain Leng
from our city police CID.

467
00:24:50,481 --> 00:24:51,281
Please have a seat.

468
00:24:57,681 --> 00:24:58,640
We called you in today

469
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,560
to learn more about Wen Yong.

470
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,400
Is there anything you can tell us?

471
00:25:03,120 --> 00:25:05,160
I've told you people many times.

472
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,400
My husband would never
solicit prostitutes.

473
00:25:07,961 --> 00:25:10,080
He disappeared on a business trip.

474
00:25:10,201 --> 00:25:11,600
It's been almost two months.

475
00:25:12,481 --> 00:25:13,800
Relevant departments

476
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:16,201
have investigated
Wen Yong's disappearance repeatedly.

477
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,840
But truly, no further leads exist.

478
00:25:19,481 --> 00:25:21,681
However, current evidence supports

479
00:25:21,681 --> 00:25:25,080
that your husband solicited prostitutes
before his disappearance.

480
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:37,761
Here are his call logs
from the past six months.

481
00:25:38,041 --> 00:25:39,041
Take a look.

482
00:25:40,721 --> 00:25:42,961
See this number highlighted in red?

483
00:25:44,041 --> 00:25:47,400
It's a known number
for an illegal massage parlor.

484
00:25:48,041 --> 00:25:49,921
Judging by the call frequency,

485
00:25:50,241 --> 00:25:52,041
your husband was a regular.

486
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:54,880
Impossible.

487
00:25:55,961 --> 00:25:57,481
You just can't find him,

488
00:25:57,481 --> 00:25:59,360
so you're smearing my husband.

489
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:06,600
Then please tell us more about Wen Yong.

490
00:26:07,001 --> 00:26:08,640
Why did he leave home that day?

491
00:26:09,281 --> 00:26:10,080
Business trip.

492
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:11,800
Official work for his company.

493
00:26:11,961 --> 00:26:13,681
Taking a train to a meeting out of town.

494
00:26:14,201 --> 00:26:16,241
Do you know what time
his train ticket was for?

495
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:17,241
6:00 PM.

496
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:19,201
How did he usually reach the station?

497
00:26:19,201 --> 00:26:20,160
By taxi.

498
00:26:28,600 --> 00:26:31,360
Please take a look.
Is this your husband Wen Yong?

499
00:26:33,441 --> 00:26:37,041
These are screenshots from cameras
along his route that day.

500
00:26:37,681 --> 00:26:39,241
Footage shows

501
00:26:39,521 --> 00:26:42,640
your husband left home and took a taxi
directly to this massage parlor.

502
00:26:45,201 --> 00:26:46,521
Timeline-wise,

503
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:49,840
he stayed inside for about 90 minutes.

504
00:26:51,281 --> 00:26:52,880
After that, he vanished without a trace.

505
00:26:59,281 --> 00:27:00,360
My husband...

506
00:27:02,761 --> 00:27:06,360
Our family has always been harmonious.

507
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,201
We both have stable jobs.

508
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:11,441
A good relationship, too.

509
00:27:12,041 --> 00:27:16,001
We've never had an argument
in all these years.

510
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:22,360
How did you get that scar?

511
00:27:27,441 --> 00:27:28,441
I fell once.

512
00:27:30,840 --> 00:27:33,320
Did Wen Yong have
anything valuable on him?

513
00:27:34,481 --> 00:27:36,001
He had several cards in his wallet.

514
00:27:36,441 --> 00:27:37,600
And a watch.

515
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:40,320
But it wasn't a high-end brand.

516
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:42,521
Worth around 10,000 yuan.

517
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:51,721
Have some.

518
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,800
This is the last place
Wen Yong was seen.

519
00:27:57,921 --> 00:27:59,160
This is the massage parlor.

520
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:01,560
Less than 50 meters this way
is the main road.

521
00:28:02,080 --> 00:28:04,640
The masseuse who attended to Wen Yong
was named Jiang Xiaohua.

522
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,120
According to her testimony,

523
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:07,400
Wen Yong was a regular of hers.

524
00:28:08,521 --> 00:28:10,201
That's where the fingerprints
were found.

525
00:28:10,201 --> 00:28:12,921
They were discovered
because there was blood nearby.

526
00:28:13,320 --> 00:28:15,600
The blood was confirmed
to be Wen Yong's.

527
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:16,481
But not much.

528
00:28:16,481 --> 00:28:18,400
It didn't appear
to be from a fatal injury.

529
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:29,160
(Yunxi Police)

530
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:32,880
Why did you bring me in again?

531
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,521
Yes.

532
00:28:34,521 --> 00:28:36,001
I was wrong before.

533
00:28:36,241 --> 00:28:37,761
I shouldn't get into that business.

534
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:40,761
But I've truly
turned over a new leaf now.

535
00:28:45,481 --> 00:28:46,400
What did you say?

536
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,360
Turned over a new leaf?

537
00:28:49,201 --> 00:28:50,360
You killed Wen Yong, right?

538
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:51,160
No.

539
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:55,400
No! H-How could it possibly be me?

540
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:56,600
Turned over a new leaf.

541
00:28:57,201 --> 00:28:59,800
Bloodstains were found at the scene.

542
00:29:00,921 --> 00:29:03,880
Since you were the last person
to see Wen Yong,

543
00:29:04,041 --> 00:29:06,761
we suspect you murdered Wen Yong

544
